{
  "response_text": "The trajectories begin at a count of 0 households with social learning at step 0, remaining near zero through approximately step 5. Between steps 5 and 30, all simulation runs exhibit a rapid, stepwise increase in the number of households engaged in social learning, with discrete jumps occurring at irregular intervals consistent with the yearly update cycle of the household decision-making sub-model. The rate of adoption varies substantially across runs: some trajectories reach saturation by step 25-30, while others continue accumulating households until approximately step 40-50.\n\nFinal plateau values range widely from approximately 18 to 54 households across the 60 total households in the system. The majority of trajectories stabilize between 40-50 households, with several runs reaching 48-54 households, indicating near-complete diffusion of social learning behavior beyond the initial 20 E-RO-SL1 agents to include E-RO and E-LBD type households. A minority of runs plateau at lower values (18-30 households), suggesting incomplete adoption. By step 60, all trajectories have stabilized, maintaining constant counts through step 100 with no further changes in household-SL status."
}

